  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6565.57 trading below the GEX flip at 6583 in a PIN regime, dealers are currently buying the dip as their long gamma position demands, creating a supportive floor around the 6550 negative gamma wall where they'll aggressively buy any further weakness. The massive positive gamma concentration at 6580 (+61.3B) acts as a brick wall above current levels, meaning dealers will increasingly sell into any rally attempt toward that strike, creating strong resistance. Watch for continued mean reversion behavior with 6550 as the key support level where dealer buying accelerates and 6580 as the ceiling where dealer selling intensifies.",
